   <script type="text/javascript">
    function loadVideo(guid, playlist) {
         videojs(guid, playlist, function () {
             var origWidth = jQuery('#' + guid).parent().data('width');
             var origHeight = jQuery('#' + guid).parent().data('height');
 
             var actualWidth = jQuery('#' + guid).parent().width();
             if (origWidth > actualWidth) {
                 this.height(origHeight * (actualWidth / origWidth));
                 this.width(actualWidth);
 
                 //Retroactively fixes an issue with resizing videos
                 //the style attribute shouldn't be on the parent
                 jQuery('#' + guid).parent().removeAttr('style');
 
             } else {
                 this.height(origHeight);
                 this.width(origWidth);
             }
             if (playlist != '{}') {
                 this.on('ended', function () {
                     this.playlist.next();
                 });
             }
 
             //fixes issue in IE when going full screen
             //video would be behind other content on the page
             this.on('enterFullWindow', function () {
                 $(this.el).parents().not('html,body').each(function () {
                     $(this)
                         .data('oldzindex', $(this).css('z-index'))
                         .css('z-index', 99999)
                         .addClass('forcedzindex');
                 });
             });
             this.on('exitFullWindow', function () {
                 $('.forcedzindex').each(function () {
                     $(this)
                         .css('z-index', $(this).data('oldzindex'))
                         .removeClass('forcedzindex')
                         .removeData('oldzindex');
                 });
 
             });
         });
     }

             jQuery.browser.msie = false;
             jQuery.browser.version = 0; if (navigator.userAgent.match(/MSIE ([0-9]+)\./)) {
                 jQuery.browser.msie = true; jQuery.browser.version = RegExp.$1;
             }
         })();
         if (jQuery.browser.msie && jQuery.browser.version <= 7) {
             //we could do something else here...
             console.log("You should really update your browser");
         }
 
         videojs.options.flash.iFrameMode = true;
         jQuery('.videoplayer > .video-js').each(function () {
             var guid = this.id;
             var playlist = jQuery('#' + guid).parent().data('playlist');
             if (playlist === undefined || playlist === null) {
                 playlist = '{}';
                 loadVideo(guid, playlist);
             }
         });
     });
   </script>

    function initMenu() {
              $('.Test2 ul').hide();
              $('.Test2 ul:first').show();
              $('.Test2 li a').click(
     function () {
         var checkElement = $(this).next();
         if ((checkElement.is('ul')) && (checkElement.is(':visible'))) {
             return false;
         }
         if ((checkElement.is('ul')) && (!checkElement.is(':visible'))) {
             $('.Test2 ul:visible').slideUp('normal');
             checkElement.slideDown('normal');
             return false;
         }
     }
     );
          }

    <script>
     $(document).ready(function () {
         function createCookie(name, value, days) {
             if (days) {
                 var date = new Date();
                 date.setTime(date.getTime() + (days * 24 * 60 * 60 * 1000));
                 var expires = "; expires=" + date.toGMTString();
             }
             else var expires = "";
             document.cookie = name + "=" + value + expires + "; path=/";
         }
 
         function readCookie(name) {
             var nameEQ = name + "=";
             var ca = document.cookie.split(';');
             for (var i = 0; i < ca.length; i++) {
                 var c = ca[i];
                 while (c.charAt(0) == ' ') c = c.substring(1, c.length);
                 if (c.indexOf(nameEQ) == 0) return c.substring(nameEQ.length, c.length);
             }
             return null;
         }
 
         function eraseCookie(name) {
             createCookie(name, "", -1);
         }
 
 
         function setColorPreference(colorPreference) {
             if (colorPreference >= 1 && colorPreference <= 4) {
                 var colors = [
                     { b: "#000000", t: "#ffffff" },
                     { b: "#ffffff", t: "#000000" },
                     { b: "#000000", t: "#ffff00" },
                     { b: "#fe0000", t: "#ffffff" }
                 ];
             }
 
             var css = "<style type='text/css'> * { background-color:" + colors[colorPreference - 1].b + " !important; color:" + colors[colorPreference - 1].t + " !important;} *:focus {color:" + colors[colorPreference - 1].t + "; border:1px dotted " + colors[colorPreference - 1].t + "}</style>";
             $('#helperStyle').html(css);
             createCookie('colorchange', colorPreference, 1);
         }
 
         function setTextSize(textSize) {
             $('#resizingText').html('<style type="text/css"> \
 		        #middle-nav ul li a, nav#top-nav li a {font-size:' + (14 + textSize) + 'pt;} \
                 h1, #content-right header {font-size:' + (24 + textSize) + 'px;} \
                 #news-list .article .news-summary, section#upcoming-events ul a, .foot2 li a, .aside-content li a{font-size:' + (13 + textSize) + 'px;} \
                 .foot2 li ul li a{font-size:' + (13 + textSize) + 'pt;} \
                 #news-list .article a.news-title{font-size:' + (14 + textSize) + 'pt;} \
                 #school-map span{font-size:' + (13 + textSize) + 'pt;} \
                 .foot2 li ul li a, .sf-vertical li a, ul.nav.navbar-nav > li > a{font-size:' + (13 + textSize) + 'px !important;} \
                 html, body, table, tr, td, div, .panel, .panel p, span, applet, object, iframe, h1, h2, h3, h4, h5, h6, p, blockquote, pre, a, abbr, acronym, address, big, cite, code, del, dfn, img, ins, kbd, q, s, samp, small, strike, sub, sup, var, i, center, dl, dt, dd, ol, ul, li, fieldset, form, label, legend, article, aside, canvas, details, embed, figure, figcaption, footer, header, footer,hgroup, menu, nav, output, ruby, section, summary, time, mark, audio, video{font-size:' + (13 + textSize) + 'pt !important; line-height: ' + (13 + textSize) + 'pt ; } \
                 </style>');
             createCookie('textsize', textSize, 1);
         }
 
         var textSize = readCookie('textsize');
         if (textSize && textSize != 0) {
             textSize = parseInt(textSize, 10);
             setTextSize(textSize);
         }
 
         var colorPreference = readCookie('colorchange');
         if (colorPreference && colorPreference != 0) {
             colorPreference = parseInt(colorPreference, 10);
             setColorPreference(colorPreference);
         }
 
         $('.vision-helper-revert').click(function () {
             eraseCookie('textsize');
             eraseCookie('colorchange');
             textSize = 0;
             $('#resizingText').empty();
             $('#helperStyle').empty();
         });
 
         $('.vision-helper-change-font-size').click(function () {
             var add = parseInt($(this).data('size-add'), 10);
             textSize += add;
             if (textSize < 1) textSize = 1;
             setTextSize(textSize);
         });
 
         $('.color-preference').click(function () {
             var colorPreference = parseInt($(this).data('color-preference'), 10);
             setColorPreference(colorPreference);
         });
     });
    </script>

        #newsTicker { background-repeat:repeat-x; background-position:top; padding-top: 3px; padding-bottom:3px; overflow:hidden; width:980px;}
         #newsTickerInner { background-color:#fff; height:27px; overflow:hidden; width:1960px; position:relative; }
         #newsTicker .tickerItemWrapper { position:absolute; top:5px; height:21px; width:980px; overflow:hidden; }
         #newsTicker .tickerItem { color:#777; font-size: 12px; font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; margin:0 auto; max-width:940px; text-align:center;}
       </style>
       <div style="height:34px;">
        <div id="newsTicker">
         <div id="newsTickerInner">
         </div>
        </div>
       </div>
       <div id="newsTickerContent" style="display:none;">
        <p>
         This page will contain the items that scroll across the news ticker at the top of the district page. Please do not delete this page. To add items to the ticker, simple create a bulleted list. Each bullet point will be an item on the news ticker.
         <span style="color:#FF0000;">
          <font size="2">
           <span style="font-size: 10pt;">
           </span>
          </font>
         </span>
        </p>
        <ul>
         <li>
          <h2>
           <span style="color:#FF0000;">
            First Day of Classes for Students August 15, 2018
           </span>
          </h2>
         </li>
        </ul>
       </div>
       <script type="text/javascript">
        $(function () {
             var items = $('#newsTickerContent li');
             var index = 0;
             var tickerTimeout = null;
             var paused = false;
 
             tickerCycle();
 
             $('#newsTicker').hover(function () {
                 paused = true;
                 if (tickerTimeout) {
                     window.clearTimeout(tickerTimeout);
                     tickerTimeout = null;
                 }
             }, function () {
                 if (paused && !tickerTimeout) {
                     tickerTimeout = window.setTimeout(function () {
                         paused = false;
                         tickerCycle();
                     }, 3000);
                 }
             });
 
             function tickerCycle() {
                 var target = $('#newsTickerInner');
                 var startOffset = 1024;
                 var item = items[index];
                 if (++index >= items.length) index = 0;
 
                 removeCurrentTickerItem(function () {
                     var tickerItemWrapper = $("<div>")
                         .addClass("tickerItemWrapper")
                         .css('left', startOffset + 'px');
                     $("<div>")
                         .addClass("tickerItem")
                         .html($(item).html())                    
                         .appendTo(tickerItemWrapper);
                     $(tickerItemWrapper).appendTo(target);
 
                     var targetOffset = '0px';
                     $(tickerItemWrapper).animate({ left: targetOffset }, 1500, 'easeOutCirc', function () {
                         if (!paused) {
                             tickerTimeout = window.setTimeout(function () {
                                 tickerCycle();
                                 tickerTimeout = null;
                             }, 3000);
                         }
                     });
                 });
             }
 
             function removeCurrentTickerItem(callback) {
                 if ($('#newsTickerInner .tickerItemWrapper').length > 0) {
                     var targetOffset = '-1024px';
                     $('#newsTickerInner .tickerItemWrapper').animate({ left: targetOffset }, 1500, 'easeOutCirc', function () {
                         $(this).remove();
                     });
                     callback();
                 } else {
                     callback();
                 }
             }
         });
       </script>

           <div class="article Newsarticle">
            <a class="news-title" id="ctl00_ctl00_MasterContent_ContentColumnMiddle_ucDnews_rep_news_ctl05_lnkTitle">
             Please welcome Mrs. Alicia Wallace to her new role as South Livingston Elementary Guidance Counselor
            </a>
            <span class="news-summary" id="ctl00_ctl00_MasterContent_ContentColumnMiddle_ucDnews_rep_news_ctl05_lblSummary">
             <p>
              <strong>
               <img alt="Wallace " src="/userfiles/2/my%20files/new%20teachers/alicia%20wallace.jpg?id=9564&amp;width=125" style="width: 125px; height: 150px;"/>
               Please welcome Mrs. Alicia Wallace to her new role as South Livingston Elementary Guidance Counselor. Mrs. Wallace has taught elementary school for 12 years, with the past two years being at SLES. She earned her bachelor’s degree in elementary education and master’s in school counseling from Murray State University. Last year, Mrs. Wallace became a National Board Certified teacher. She lives in the Reidland area with her husband, Bradley, and twin sons, Eli and Ean. We appreciate Mrs. Wallace’s dedication to Livingston County students and are confidant in the guidance she will provide them in her new role.
              </strong>
             </p>
            </span>
           </div>
           <div class="article Newsarticle">
            <a class="news-title" id="ctl00_ctl00_MasterContent_ContentColumnMiddle_ucDnews_rep_news_ctl06_lnkTitle">
             We are proud to partner with Jobs for America’s Graduates (JAG) and name Jennifer Henson as JAG Specialist
            </a>
            <span class="news-summary" id="ctl00_ctl00_MasterContent_ContentColumnMiddle_ucDnews_rep_news_ctl06_lblSummary">
             <p>
              <strong>
               <img alt="JAG" src="/userfiles/2/my%20files/new%20teachers/jennifer%20henson.jpg?id=9559&amp;width=131" style="width: 131px; height: 150px;"/>
               We are proud to partner with Jobs for America’s Graduates (JAG) and name Jennifer Henson as JAG Specialist. JAG is a state-based national non-profit organization dedicated to preventing dropouts among young people who are most at-risk. In more than three decades of operation, JAG has delivered consistent, compelling results – helping nearly three-quarters of a million young people stay in school through graduation, pursue postsecondary education, and secure quality entry-level jobs leading to career advancement opportunities.
              </strong>
             </p>
             <p>
              <strong>
               As a special education paraprofessional this past year, Mrs. Henson has been assisting students with work readiness skills and employment opportunities. She has been married to her husband for 13 years and together they have three children. She earned her bachelor’s degree from Murray State University in 2013 and is working on a master’s with concentration in learning and behavior disorders from the University of the Cumberlands. We are certain the experience she brings to this role and her dedication to Live RED will be beneficial to Livingston students as they transition into young adulthood. We welcome Mrs. Henson in her new role.
              </strong>
             </p>
            </span>
           </div>

               <sup>

She is a 2008 graduate of LCHS and a 2011 graduate of Murray State University with a bachelor’s degree in business administration. She has worked in healthcare for the last 5 years but is excited for the opportunity to work in her home county. She is married to her husband, Justin, and together they have one son, Jase. They are owners of Smokey D’s of Smithland which keeps them busy, but when they do have free time they love to be outdoors. We are glad to have Mrs. Smith with us and are confident the skills brings to the LCMS afterschool and summer programs will greatly benefit our students.

            <a class="news-title" id="ctl00_ctl00_MasterContent_ContentColumnMiddle_ucDnews_rep_news_ctl12_lnkTitle">
             Please welcome Kristy Nelson as the Systems Officer for Livingston County Public Schools
            </a>
            <span class="news-summary" id="ctl00_ctl00_MasterContent_ContentColumnMiddle_ucDnews_rep_news_ctl12_lblSummary">
             <p>
              <span style='font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;color:black'>
               <img alt="Kristi " src="/userfiles/2/my%20files/boe/kristy.jpg?id=9545&amp;width=120" style="width: 120px; height: 150px;"/>
               Please welcome Kristy Nelson as the Systems Officer for Livingston County Public Schools. Mrs. Nelson has a master’s degree in Elementary Teaching from the University of the Cumberlands, as well as Teacher Leadership with a Literacy concentration from Murray State University. She has taught in multiple states over the course of her teaching career and was the director of a non-profit, which brings a unique perspective to her position. She has presented at multiple state and local conferences including the Kentucky Reading Conference, Murray State College and Career Summit, and a guest lecturer on close reading at the Kentucky Reading Project. During her time with Christian County Public Schools, she led professional development with Teachers Intentionally Leading Teachers (TILT) on using curriculum to meet standards, guided reading, and the implementation of literature circles. As the Systems Officer, she is dedicated to helping Livingston County reach for excellence as we LiveRED.
               <o:p>
               </o:p>
              </span>
             </p>
            </span>
           </div>
           <div class="article Newsarticle">
            <a class="news-title" id="ctl00_ctl00_MasterContent_ContentColumnMiddle_ucDnews_rep_news_ctl13_lnkTitle">
             Livingston County Schools is honored to name Amy Ramage as the district’s Chief Education Officer.
            </a>
            <span class="news-summary" id="ctl00_ctl00_MasterContent_ContentColumnMiddle_ucDnews_rep_news_ctl13_lblSummary">
             <p>
              <strong>
               <img alt="Amy " src="/userfiles/2/my%20files/boe/amy/amy%20ramage.jpg?id=9563&amp;width=120" style="width: 120px; height: 150px;"/>
               Livingston County Schools is honored to name Amy Ramage as the district’s Chief Education Officer. The position was created in order to clarify our system of governance and leadership for continuous improvement in district/school transformations that are aligned with school, district, and state priorities.  As part of the district leadership team, Mrs. Ramage will assist in defining and expanding school autonomy, personalizing teaching and learning, improving the use of data, and exploring innovative non-traditional pathways for schools. She will meet regularly with students, families and other stakeholders to generate ideas and create consensus around innovative strategies to meet individualized student needs and to remove barriers.  She will work with staff to ensure knowledge, skills, and attitudes (those defined by our community as valuable contributions to student development) are used to guide Livingston County students into able and responsible adult citizens. Mrs. Ramage has served Livingston County Schools and the community for 5 years as the district DPP and 18 years as an educator.  She will continue her duties as DPP.  We are confident with her ability to lead the district with excellence and we appreciate her continued commitment to the improvement of educational services provided to the students and families of Livingston County Schools.
              </strong>
             </p>
            </span>
           </div>
